        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I think it would be extermely useful to have the abbility to cache actions in the same way as Zend_Cache_Forntend_Page. In init() i would setup cacheable actions, options and if cache found it would inject it directly to response.... \n\nI think now I can use Zend_Cache_Frontend_Class, but it's just too complicated to handle all the stuff around - like response segments... Or Zend_Cache_Output, but it still doesn't do the job. "
