            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25454",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't understand.\n\nIs it something to implement in Zend_Cache or in Zend MVC stuff ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-27T11:53:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-27T11:53:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25457",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not sure where it would be the best place form implementation. My point is, that there is no easy way of chaching one specific Controller and\/or some of his Actions. You can do it via URL or via caching the class, but no easy \"one array config\" solution. \n\nI think of something like \n\nZend_Cache::registerControllerCache($array);\nIt would setup the cache, save it in Registry and then use it in the dispatching process to find whether the action needs to be regenerated or not. Am I clear?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-27T12:03:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-27T12:03:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'll try to write the code I'd like to use:\n\n{code:title=bootstrap|borderStyle=solid}\n$frontendOptions = (array('index','index','default'),array('about','index','default'));\n$cache = Zend_Cache::factory('Controller','File',$frontendOptions,$backendOptions);\n\/\/save it to Registry to some specific key\n$frontController->dispatch();\n{code}\n\n{code:title=somewhere in dispatch process|borderStyle=solid}\n\/\/get from registry (should be auto - like Zend_Translate)\nif($cache->isCachedRequest($request)){ \n\/\/ check if already cached and send stored cache to response object\n} else {\n\/\/ continue normally\n}\n{code}\n\n{code:title=internally just before saving action result to response object|borderStyle=solid}\nif($cache->isCachedRequest($request)){ \n$cache->save($responseData);\n\/\/ including response segment, view renderer state, noRender, etc...\n}\n\/\/send to response\n{code}\nDoes this help? Is there any way to do this this easily with current Zend_Cache components?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "name": "tomas.fejfar@gmail.com",
                        "displayName": "Tom\u00e1\u0161 Fejfar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T09:30:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T09:30:57.000+0000"
                },
